```java
public class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n < 1) {
            return false;
        }

        while (n % 3 == 0) {
            n /= 3;
        }

        return n == 1;
    }
}
```

If you want to solve it without using a loop or recursion, you can use the properties of logarithms. If n is a power of 3, then log3(n) would be an integer. To calculate log base 3, we can use the change of base formula: log3(n) = ln(n) / ln(3). As we don't have exact precision with floating point numbers, we check if the exponent, when rounded to the nearest integer, still yields the original number when used as the exponent of 3.

```java
public class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        double epsilon = 1e-10; // precision tolerance
        double logRes = Math.log(n) / Math.log(3);
        return Math.abs(logRes - Math.round(logRes)) < epsilon;
    }
}
```

